This paper deals with data transformation capabilities associated with schemas, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new algebraic query language, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of graphs and path equations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the query language using key-generation operations, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
